<inglise> Whereas the establishment of the internal market in accordance with Article 8a of the Treaty requires the creation of an area without internal frontiers in which the free movement of goods, persons, services and capital is ensured; whereas the internal market requires changes in the legislation on value added tax as provided in Article 99 of the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: vastavalt asutamislepingu artiklile 8a on siseturu rajamiseks vaja luua sisepiirideta ala, kus on tagatud kaupade, isikute, teenuste ja kapitali vaba liikumine; vastavalt austamislepingu artiklile 99 on siseturu toimimiseks vaja muuta k&auml;ibemaksu k&auml;sitlevaid &otilde;igusakte; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order to avoid tax revenue losses for Member States the tax harmonization measures taken to complete the internal market and for the transitional period must include the establishment of a common system for the exchange of information on intra-Community transactions between the competent authorities of the Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriikide maksutulu v&auml;henemise v&auml;ltimiseks peaks siseturu v&auml;ljakujundamise eesm&auml;rgil ja &uuml;leminekuperioodi jooksul v&otilde;etavate maksude &uuml;htlustamise meetmete hulka kuuluma &uuml;hise teabevahetuss&uuml;steemi loomine, mis kajastaks liikmesriikide p&auml;devate asutuste &uuml;hendusesiseseid tehinguid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order to permit the abolition of fiscal controls at internal frontiers in accordance with the aims set out in Article 8a of the Treaty the transitional value added tax system introduced by Directive 91/680/EEC (4), amending Directive 77/388/EEC (5), must be effectively established without the risk of fraud which might cause distortions of competition; </inglise>
<eesti> maksukontrolli kaotamiseks sisepiiril koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu artiklis 8a p&uuml;stitatud eesm&auml;rkidega tuleb t&otilde;husalt rakendada direktiiviga 91/680/EM&Uuml; (4) (millega muudetakse direktiivi 77/388/EM&Uuml; (5)) kehtestatud &uuml;leminekuperioodi k&auml;ibemaksus&uuml;steemi, v&auml;ltides pettuste ohtu, mis v&otilde;iksid p&otilde;hjustada konkurentsimoonutusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Regulation provides for a common system for the exchange of information on intra-Community transactions, supplementing Directive 77/799/EEC (6), as last amended by Directive 79/1070/EEC (7), and intended to serve tax purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega n&auml;hakse ette direktiivi 77/799/EM&Uuml; (6) (viimati muudetud direktiiviga 79/1070/EM&Uuml; (7)) s&auml;tteid t&auml;iendava &uuml;hendusesiseseid tehinguid kajastava &uuml;hise maksualase teabes&uuml;steemi loomine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Member States should provide the Commission with any value added tax information which may be of interest at Community level; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriigid peaksid esitama komisjonile kogu k&auml;ibemaksualase teabe, mis v&otilde;iks olla oluline &uuml;henduse tasandil; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the establishment of a common system of administrative cooperation may affect individuals' legal positions, in particular because of the exchange of information concerning their tax positions; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;hise halduskoost&ouml;&ouml;s&uuml;steemi loomine v&otilde;ib m&otilde;jutada &uuml;ksikisikute &otilde;iguslikku seisundit eelk&otilde;ige nende maksualaste andmete vahetuse t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas care must be taken to ensure that the provisions concerning the control of indirect taxes are in balance with administrations' needs for effective control and the administrative burdens imposed on taxable persons; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleb hoolitseda, et oleks tagatud tasakaal kaudsete maksude kontrollimist k&auml;sitlevate s&auml;tete ja ametiasutuste t&otilde;husa kontrolli vajaduse ning maksustatavatele isikutele pandud halduskoormuse vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the operation of such a system requires the establishment of a standing committee on administrative cooperation; </inglise>
<eesti> niisuguse s&uuml;steemi toimimine n&otilde;uab halduskoost&ouml;&ouml;ga tegeleva alalise komitee moodustamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Member States and the Commission must establish an effective system for the electronic storage and transmission of certain data for value added tax control purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriigid ja komisjon peavad k&auml;ibemaksu kontrollimiseks looma teatavate andmete jaoks t&otilde;husa s&auml;ilitamis- ja edastamiss&uuml;steemi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas care must be taken to ensure that information provided in the course of such collaboration is not disclosed to unauthorized persons, so that the basic rights of citizens and undertakings are safeguarded; whereas it is therefore necessary that an authority receiving such information should not, without the authorization of the authority supplying it, use it for purposes other than taxation or to facilitate legal proceedings for failure to comply with the tax laws of the Member States concerned; whereas the receiving authority must also accord such information the same degree of confidentiality as it enjoyed in the Member State which provided it, if the latter so requires; </inglise>
<eesti> isikute ja ettev&otilde;tete p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste kaitseks tuleb hoolitseda, et selleks koost&ouml;&ouml;ks esitatav teave ei satuks k&otilde;rvaliste isikute k&auml;tte; seet&otilde;ttu on vaja, et niisugust teavet saav asutus ei kasutaks teavet seda esitanud asutuse loata muul eesm&auml;rgil kui maksustamiseks v&otilde;i kohtumenetluste h&otilde;lbustamiseks, kui rikutakse asjaomase liikmesriigi maksuseadusi; teavet saav asutus peab tagama sellele samasuguse salastatuse astme kui teavet esitav liikmesriik, kui viimane seda n&otilde;uab; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Member States and the Commission must collaborate on the continuous analysis of cooperation procedures and the pooling of the experience gained in the fields in question, with the aims of improving those procedures and drawing up appropriate Community rules, </inglise>
