<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authority of each Member State shall maintain an electronic data base in which it shall store and process the information that it collects in accordance with Article 22 (6) (b) of Directive 77/388/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused peavad andmebaasi, milles hoitakse ja t&ouml;&ouml;deldakse direktiivi 77/388/EM&Uuml; artikli 22 l&otilde;ike 6 punkti b kohaselt kogutud teavet. </eesti>
<inglise> To allow the use of this information in the procedures provided for in this Regulation the information shall be stored for at least five years after the end of the calendar year in which access to the information was to be granted. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle teabe kasutamise v&otilde;imaldamiseks k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud toimingutes tuleb seda teavet s&auml;ilitada v&auml;hemalt viis aastat p&auml;rast selle kalendriaasta l&otilde;ppu, mil tuli tagada juurdep&auml;&auml;s teabele. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that their data bases are kept up to date, complete and accurate. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et andmebaas on ajakohastatud, t&auml;ielik ja t&auml;pne. </eesti>
<inglise> Under the procedure laid down in Article 10 criteria shall be defined to determine what amendments that are not significant, material or useful need not be made. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 10 s&auml;testatud korras m&auml;&auml;ratakse kriteeriumid, mille alusel otsustatakse, missugused muudatused ei ole asjakohased, olulised v&otilde;i kasulikud ja mis v&otilde;ib seet&otilde;ttu tegemata j&auml;tta. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> From the data collected in accordance with paragraph 1, the competent authority of a Member State shall obtain directly and without delay from each Member State, or may have direct access to, the following information: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt kogutud andmetest saab liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus vahetult ja viivitamata iga liikmesriigi kohta j&auml;rgmist teavet, millele tal v&otilde;ib olla ka vahetu juurdep&auml;&auml;s: </eesti>
<inglise> - the value added tax identification numbers issued by the Member State receiving the information, and </inglise>
<eesti> - k&auml;ibemaksukohustuslase registrinumbrid, mille on andnud teavet saav liikmesriik, </eesti>
<inglise> - the total value of all intra-Community supplies of goods made to the persons to whom those numbers were issued by all operators identified for the purposes of value added tax in the Member State providing the information; the values shall be expressed in the currency of the Member State providing the information and shall relate to calendar quarters. </inglise>
<eesti> - nende &uuml;hendusesiseste kaubatarnete koguv&auml;&auml;rtus, mis on registrinumbri saanud isikutele teinud need isikud, kellele on teavet andnud liikmesriik andnud k&auml;ibemaksukohustuse registrinumbri; v&auml;&auml;rtused v&auml;ljendatakse kalendriaasta kvartalite l&otilde;ikes teavet andva liikmesriigi v&auml;&auml;ringus. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> From the data collected in accordance with paragraph 1 and solely in order to combat tax fraud, the competent authority of a Member State shall, wherever it considers it necessary for the control of intra-Community acquisitions of goods, obtain directly and without delay, or have direct access to, the following information: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt kogutud andmetest, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on &uuml;ksnes maksupettuste &auml;rahoidmine, saab liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus, kui ta peab vajalikuks kontrollida &uuml;hendusesisest kaupade omandamist, vahetult ja viivitamata iga liikmesriigi kohta j&auml;rgmist teavet, millele tal v&otilde;ib olla ka vahetu juurdep&auml;&auml;s: </eesti>
<inglise> - the value added tax identification numbers of all persons who have made the supplies referred to in the second indent of paragraph 2, and </inglise>
<eesti> - nende isikute k&auml;ibemaksukohustuslase registrinumbrid, kes on teinud l&otilde;ike 2 teises taandes nimetatud tarned, </eesti>
<inglise> - the total value of such supplies from each such person to each person to whom one of the value added tax identification numbers referred to in the first indent of paragraph 2 has been issued; the values shall be expressed in the currency of the Member State providing the information and shall relate to calendar quarters. </inglise>
<eesti> - nende kaubatarnete koguv&auml;&auml;rtus, mille on teinud k&otilde;ik nimetatud isikud nendele isikutele, kellele on antud &uuml;ks l&otilde;ike 2 esimeses taandes osutatud k&auml;ibemaksukohustuslase registrinumbritest; v&auml;&auml;rtused v&auml;ljendatakse kalendriaasta kvartalite l&otilde;ikes teavet andva liikmesriigi v&auml;&auml;ringus. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the competent authority of a Member State is obliged to grant access to information under this Article it shall, as regards the information referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3, do so within three months of the end of the calendar quarter to which the information relates. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus on vastavalt k&auml;esolevale artiklile kohustatud tagama juurdep&auml;&auml;su teabele, siis l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud teabe puhul peab ta seda tegema kolme kuu jooksul p&auml;rast selle kvartali l&otilde;ppu, mille kohta nimetatud teave k&auml;ib. </eesti>
<inglise> By way of derogation from this rule, where information is added to a data base in the circumstances provided for in paragraph 1, access to such additions shall be granted as quickly as possible and in any event no more than three months after the end of the quarter in which the additional information was collected; the conditions under which access to the corrected information may be granted shall be defined by means of the procedure laid down in Article 10. </inglise>
